    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><h3>Problem description</h3>\n<p>Raj, the love of Simran's life is waiting at an airport exactly <b>'N'</b> steps away from her. Simran is running to meet the love of her life.\nShe takes 1, 2 or 3 steps per second . She can also take some rest to catch a breath, i.e 0 steps per second.\nBut the path of love is not always easy and she might fall a few times while running. If she falls more than <b>'M'</b> times, she would be too injured and won't be able to make it.\nIn the second that she falls, she isn't able to take any step.\nThe flight they have to take will depart exactly after <b>'K'</b> seconds, so she cannot be any more late.\nShe should not run beyond the airport i.e take more than <b>'N'</b> steps as it would break Raj's heart.\n\nFormally, to make her love story successful, she needs to cover exactly <b>'N'</b> steps in exactly <b>'K'</b> seconds, without falling more than <b>'M'</b> times, with the allowed step sizes being 0, 1, 2 and 3.\n\nDwij, a dear friend of Raj and Simran is obsessed with combinatorics and is interested to know the number of ways she can do so (modulo 1000000007). Help Dwij find the solution.\nAlso, Pray for Simran and Raj. Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge :) </p>\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The first line of the input contains <b>'T'</b>, the number of test cases.\n<br>Next <b>'T'</b> lines follow, each containing 3 space separated integers <b>N, K </b> and <b>M</b> for that testcase.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For each test case output the number of ways <b>(modulo 1000000007)</b> on a separate line.</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>1000</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>1000000000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>K</b> \u2264 <b>300</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>M</b> \u2264 <b>300</b></li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n\n2\n5 3 1\n4 3 0\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n\n18\n12\n\n</pre>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<pre>\n<p>In the first testcase, the valid sequence of steps taken are:\n(0, 2, 3)\n(0, 3, 2)\n(2, 0, 3)\n(2, 3, 0)\n(3, 0, 2)\n(3, 2, 0)\n(Fall, 2, 3)\n(Fall, 3, 2)\n(2, Fall, 3)\n(2, 3, Fall)\n(3, Fall, 2)\n(3, 2, Fall)\n(1, 1, 3)\n(1, 3, 1)\n(3, 1, 1)\n(2, 2, 1)\n(2, 1, 2)\n(1, 2, 2)\nTotal 18 possible valid sequences / ways.\n\nIn the second testcase, the valid sequence of steps taken are:\n(0, 1, 3)\n(0, 3, 1)\n(1, 0, 3)\n(1, 3, 0)\n(3, 0, 1)\n(3, 1, 0)\n(1, 1, 2)\n(1, 2, 1)\n(2, 1, 1)\n(2, 2, 0)\n(2, 0, 2)\n(0, 2, 2)\nTotal 12 possible valid sequences / ways.</p>\n</pre>",
